On june 3, 2011
Piemaster
Further explanation:

The 'time trick' is basically just an exploitation of the turn mechanic. Your 'turn' can be started at any time, but your dinos can act at any time between then and when your next turn is started.

While your dino only gets one turn per day (okay, per 23 hours) that doesn't mean its moves/fights have to be at exact 23 hour intervals. For example, if you start your new turn at 5pm, your dino could choose not to move until 4pm the following day. Then he could move, you could start your *next* turn and then move your dino again straight away. There are a number of applications of this trick, including:

1. Keeping your dino at the FoY for as long as possible to take advantage of the free 5HP every night. For example, during Madam X's first mission, you can move to the FoY, then wait until right before your next turn to move to Frish Port, then move back to the FoY immediately, before waiting until the start of the following turn to move back to Brute Force. You can do exactly the same for the following mission and your dino will gain 5HP every single night while you're doing those two missions.

2. You can start resting at the start of a turn then, after starting your next turn, wait until the last possible moment before cancelling the rest and moving/fighting before then starting your next turn. You therefore gain 46 HP (92 with Priest) in exchange for only 1 turn of resting.

3. You can move back and forth from Sticky Swamp without ever wasting a turn regardless of the day of the week. For example, if you are at the Swamp and it is Saturday, just wait until Sunday morning and move just before starting your next turn.

4. At the clinic you can heal a group of 3 dinos without ever having to waste a turn fighting. Move to the clinic, heal straight away, then heal the following day before starting your next turn and then heal the last one a day later before moving the group back, then start the next turn and move back to Dino Town.

There are probably others that I am forgetting right now, but that's the gist of it.

On june 9, 2011
Kayin
It's protecting your dinoz once from indirect damage over 10. A-Skills are mostly direct damage.
Example 1: Tricky/Fatal secondary effect, if it does over 10 damage could trigger Danger Detector.
Example 2: Poison tick, unless poison does less than 10 damage, it will trigger once for first damage tick.
Example 3: Elemental Master Wood Mission: It protects your dinoz from Cursed Wand damage, but don't prevent your dinoz from being cursed.
Example 4: It will prevented from being scaled.

On june 13, 2011
AndySQdancer
Mutoh, you have a lot to learn about Spherical Skills. Try reading some of the Clans' Public Pages about Spheres and Spherical Skills. A single Dinoz can have a total of 15 Spherical Skills, 3 from each of the 5 Elements. As long as the Sphere is in the Inventory, it is available for use by any of your Dinoz. Once your Dinoz uses a Sphere, that Dinoz only acquires that Sphere’s Skill (there is no way it can be used again) – Level of Shperical Skill is determined by the Element of the Sphere and whether it is the 1st, 2nd, or 3rd Sphere used of a particular Element giving your Dinoz the 1st, 2nd, or 3rd Spherical Skill for that Element, respectively. A Sphere is obtained by a Dinoz as a Reward for doing All of the Elemental Master’s Missions or buying them on the Market from a Master whose Dinoz has been Rewarded a Sphere. Each Dinoz can only be Rewarded One Random Sphere.

[977879]
Can someone exsplain how movement in katacombs work. I know you can only heal in certain locations. I've seen the maps and want to figure out how long it will take.
On september 13, 2011
Kayin
Once a new turn or an Irma potion you can move your dinoz or group of dinoz with arrows on keyboard (or use the arrows on the screen but it will be gruesome to click that much). You can move until you fight once. To continue, wait a new turn or use an Irma.

To heal, you need to go on the greenish things, once there go on your dinoz page and heal (or buy items and then heal). Once you return to your catacombs screen, the healing spot will be used forever, whether you have healed your dinoz or not.

Adrole
once a dinoz is frozen how do you unfreeze him do you send another dino to the gorges or what

When frozen they dissappear from the side bar, but you can still select the dinoz from your "My Account" page and they will appear like any other dinoz would then you just need to click to unfreeze them (which takes until the next day).

So no you do not need to move another dinoz to deep gorges.

Also when you freeze a dinoz any combat gear you leave on him you can take it from him whenever you want (but you cannot give him any new combat gear while frozen) This is especially useful for good combat gear from Magnetic Steppes, Monster Island etc.

al-Aqsa
Jengas
I'm wanting to buy two dinoz and train them together.
I notice you have bought some dinos aready but early on I'd advice you to focus on U-skills whilst still figuring things out. You can't really mess up an U-skill dino.

In case you don't know about these already I'll slap together a cliffsNotes. U-skills are skills that effect your account outside of combat providing small perks and advantages, these range from vital to relatively worthless. There are 7 U-skills in the game: Leader (more active dinos), Engineer (more equipment slots), Merchant (cheaper items), Priest (faster resting), Cooker (more HP from health items), Storekeeper (more inventory space) and Professor (more XP). It's debatable which ones are most important for a new player but you should at least aim for Leader for more dinos ergo more gold. Plenty of clans have some information about these in their Clan pages so I urge you to snoop around a bit.

Stinkymeat
Imthewind:

First off, you need to get the double skill skill from Madame X before you level again. You have sapper + vaporous form that give you an unlock on bubble.

As to plunging attack:

Nice thing is that it is a skill that goes through other bubbles for full damage, where water cannon and gel do not. Also, depending upon how much water vs. air you roll will answer it a lot. I can tell you that even with my Bubble Kabukis in the high 30s I still turn off water cannon because of its sad damage. You just won't ever have enough to really make it work well. I'd rather have the physical attack (made better with specialist) than gel/water cannon. Those are good picks so you can get petrification and kar sheer, but I wouldn't say those skills are better than plunging attack.

However, you essentially have to think about how far you are willing to push your Kabuki. In a year, with some concentration (if you aren't spending real money) you can get to about level 40. If you are optimizing to have the most viable level 40 possible, I don't think plunging attack fits into that at all (nor jump, really). But since you are down that path, both plunging attack and stealth are decent skills that you shouldn't turn down, in my opinion.
